<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-23T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-23T15:36:00-05:00" n="1082" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1082">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/270.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-23T14:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Press reports that the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Maryland</hi> is now on
                            the way to Los Mochis are giving Minister Foreign Affairs much concern.
                            He says Mexican Government has no objection to Americans there being
                            taken away by the United States, but on account of effect upon public
                            opinion earnestly hopes that vessel may be revenue cutter or
                            transport.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>